workout:name: Elevated
workout:description: Start: Get into modified push up position, with your hands on an elevated surface. /n 1) Lower your body until it is inches away from the ground. /n 2) Push yourself back up, reapeat motion.

workout:name: Elevated Spring
workout:description: Start: Get into modified push up position with your hands on an elevated surface. /n 1) Lower body until it is inches away from the elevated surface. 2) On the way up, push as hard as you can and lift yourself off the elevated surface. /n 3) Return to original position and repeat.

workout:name: Elevated Triangle
workout:description: Start: Get into modified push up position, with your hands in the shape of a triangle, under your chest. /n 1) Lower body until it is inches away from the elevated surface. /n 2) Lift yourself back up to original starting position.

workout:name: Elevated Isometric 3 Count
workout:description: Start: Get into modified push up position, with your hands on an elevated surface. /n 1) Lower yourself halfway and pause for 3 seconds, then continue until you are inches from the elevated surface. /n 2) Push yourself back up, repeat.

workout:name: Elevated Eccentric 4 Count
workout:description: Start: Get into modified push up position, with your hands on an elevated surface. /n 1) Lower yourself slowly to the elevated surface, taking 4 seconds to reach the bottom. /n 2) Push yourself back up, repeat.

workout:name: Traditional
workout:description: Start: Place your hands under your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders. Have only your knees and hands on the ground. Keep a straight back and weight on the outside of your hands.

workout:name: Isometric 3 count
workout:description: Start: Get into modified push up position. /n 1) Lower yourself to the ground but pause halfway for 3 seconds. /n 2) Continue all the way down and push yourself back up. Repeat

workout:name: Eccentric 4 count
workout:description: Start: Get into modified push up position. /n 1) Lower yourself slowly to the ground, taking 4 seconds for your chest to reach the floor. /n 2) Push yourself back up, repeat.

workout:name: Triangle
workout:description: Start: Get into modified push up position, with your hands in the shape of a triangle under your chest. /n 1) Lower yourself all the way to the ground. /n 2) Finish push up, repeat.

workout:name: Against Wall
workout:description: Start: Place your hands slightly lower than your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders, on a wall. You should be at a slight angle. Hold a straight back. /n 1) Lower upper body towards wall, hold straight back throughout. /n 2) Raise body to original position, repeat.

workout:name: Wall Push Off
workout:description: Start: Get into wall push up position. /n 1) Lower upper body towards wall, hold straight back throughout. /n 2) When you push back up, push yourself off the wall, then land on the wall, repeat.

workout:name: Wall Isometric 3 Count
workout:description: Start: Get into wall push up position. Lower upper body to the wall, pausing for 3 seconds half way. /n 2) Go down as far as you can, then finish the push up, repeat.

workout:name: Wall Eccentric 4 Count
workout:description: Start: Get into wall push up position. /n 1) Lower upper body slowly towards towards the wall, taking 4 seconds for body to reach the lowest point. /n 2) Push your self back up, repeat.

workout:name: Hand Elevation
workout:description: Start: Get into traditional push up position, with your hands on an elevated surface, slightly wider than your shoulder, under your chest. /n 1) Lower your body until your chest is inches away from the elevated surface. /n 2) Push yourself back up into original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Traditional
workout:description: Start: Place your hands under your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders. Have only your toes and palms on the floor, keeping a straight back, with the weight on the outside of your hands. /n 1) Lower your whole body by bending your elbows. Elbows should bend towads your feet. Lower until your chest is inches away from the floor.  /n 2) Raise yourself back up, maintaining a straight back.

workout:name: 1 Foot
workout:description: Start: Get into traditional push up position, with one foot off the ground. /n 1) Lower your body until it is inches away from the ground. /n 2) Push yourself back to original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Feet Elevation
workout:description: Start: Get into traditional push up position, with your feet on an elevated surface. /n 1) Lower yourself until your head is inches away from the ground. /n 2) Push yourself back to original starting position.

workout:name: 1 Foot Elevation
workout:description: Start: Get into traditional push up position, with one foot on an elevated surface. /n 1) Lower yourself until your head is inches away from the floor. /n 2) Push yourself back up to original position.

workout:name: Stability Ball Elevation
workout:description: Start: Place your feet on a stability ball, and hands underneath your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders. Maintain a straight back. /n 1) Lower yourself to the ground until your head is inches away. /n 2) Push yourself back to original starting position.

workout:name: Isometric 3 Count
workout:description: Start: Get into traditional push up position. /n 1) Lower your self half way and pause for 3 seconds. /n 2) Continue down until your chest is inches away from the floor. /n 3) Push yourself back up to original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Eccentric 4 Count
workout:description: Start: Get into traditional push up position. /n 1) Lower yourself slowly to the ground, taking 4 seconds for your body to reach the lowest point. /n 2) Push yourself back to original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Stability Ball 1 Foot
workout:description: Start: Place one foot on a stability ball, and your hands on the ground, underneath your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders. /n 1) Lower yourself until your head is inches away from the floor. /n 2) Push yourself back up to original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Stability Ball on Hands
workout:description: Start: Place both hands on a stability ball, with your feet on the ground. Maintain a flat back. /n 1) Lower your self until your are inches away from the stability ball. /n 2) Push yourself back up to original starting position, repeat.

Start: Get into traditional push up position. /n 1) Lower your self until your chest is inches away from the floor. /n 2) Push your self half way up and hold for 2 seconds. /n 3) Drop back until your chest is inches away from the floor. /n 4) Push your self back up to original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Elevated Isometric 3 Count
workout:description: Start: Get into traditional push up position, with your feet on an elevated surface. /n 1) Lower yourself halfway, and hold for 3 seconds. /n 2) Continue lowering yourself until your are inches off the ground. /n 3) Push yourself back up to original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: elevated Eccentric 4 Count
workout:description: Start: Get into traditional push up position, with your feet on an elevated surface. /n 1) Slowly lower yourself to the ground, taking 4 seconds to reach the lowest point. /n 2) Push yourself back up to original starting position.

workout:name: Double Stability Ball
workout:description: Start: Place the top of your feet and both hands on stability balls, maintain a flat back. /n 1) Lower yourself until your chest is inches away from the front stability ball. /n 2) Push yourself back up to original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Traditonal Push Up
workout:description: Start: Place both hands on the flat side of a BOSU ball, under your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders. Maintain a flat back, with only your toes on the ground. /n 1) Lower your body until your chest is inches away from the BOSU ball. /n 2) Push yourself back up to original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Feet Elevated
workout:description: Start: Place both hands on the flat side of a BOSU ball, under your chest, slightly wider than your shouldersl, and your feet on an elevated surface. /n 1) Lower yourself until your chest is inches off of the BOSU ball. /n 2) Push yourself back up to original starting position.

workout:name: Isometric 3 Count Push Up
workout:description: Start: Place both hands on the flat side of a BOSU ball, under your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders. Toes on the ground. /n 1) Lower yourself halfway, and hold for 3 seconds. /n 2) Continue until your chest is inches away from the BOSU ball. /n 3) Push yourself back up to orginal starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Eccentric 4 Count Push Up
workout:description: Start: Place both hands on the flat side of a BOSU ball, under your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders. /n 1) Slowly lower yourself, taking 4 seconds to reach the lowest point. /n 2) Push yourself back up to original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: BOSU + Stability Ball
workout:description: Start: Place both hands on the flat side of a BOSU ball, under your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders, with top of your feet on a stability ball. /n 1) Lower yourself until your chest is inches away from the BOSU ball. /n 2) Push yourself back up to original starting position.

Start: Place both hands on the flat side of a BOSU ball, under your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders, toes on the ground. /n 1) Lower yourself until you are inches away from the BOSU ball. /n 2) Push yourself halfway up, and hold for 2 seconds. /n 3) Return to the lowest point, and push yourself back up to the original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Triangle
workout:description: Start: Place both hands in the center of the flat side of a BOSU ball, in the shape of a triangle under your chest. Have your arms fully extended, maintain a flat back, and have your toes on the ground. /n 1) Lower yourself until your chest is inches away from the BOSU ball. /n 2) Push yourself back up to the original starting position.

workout:name: Wall
workout:description: Start: Place your hands on a wall, in the shape of a triangle, slightly lower than your chest. Have your arms extended. Your body should be at an angle /n 1) Lower your self until your head is inches away from the wall. /n 2) Push yourself back out to the original starting position.

workout:name: Modified Elevated
workout:description: Start: Get into modified push up position, with your hands in the shape of a triangle, under your chest. /n 1) Lower body until it is inches away from the elevated surface. /n 2) Lift yourself back up to original starting position.

workout:name: Modified
workout:description: Start: Get into modified push up position, with your hands in the shape of a triangle under your chest. /n 1) Lower yourself all the way to the ground. /n 2) Finish push up, repeat.

workout:name: Traditional
workout:description: Start: Place your hands in the shape of a triangle, underneath your chest, with the weight on the outside of your hands and arms extended. Maintain a flat back and have your toes on the ground. /n 1) Lower yourself by bending your elbows, which should be pointed towards your feet. /n 2) Push yourself back up to the original starting position.

workout:name: Isometric 3 Count
workout:description: Start: Place your hands in the shape of a triangle, underneath your chest, with the weight on the outside of your hands and arms extended. Maintain a flat back and have your toes on the ground. /n 1) Lower yourself halfway to the ground, and pause for 3 seconds. /n 2) After the pause, go until your chest is inches away from the floor. /n 3) Push yourself back up to the original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Eccentric 4 Count
workout:description: Start: Place your hands in the shape of a triangle, underneath your chest, with the weight on the outside of your hands and arms extended. Maintain a flat back and have your toes on the ground. /n 1) Slowly lower your self to the ground, taking 4 seconds to reach the lowest point. /n 2) Once you reach the bottom, push your self back up to the original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Elevation
workout:description: Start: Place your feet on an elevated surface, your hands in the shape of a triangle, underneath your chest, with the weight on the outside of your hands and arms extended. Maintain a flat back. /n 1) Lower yourself until your head is inches away from the ground. /n 2) Push yourself back up to the original starting position.

workout:name: Modified Elevated
workout:description: Start: From your knees, place your hands on an elevated surface, under your chest, in an offset position. Move one hand slightly forward, and one hand slightly back./n 1) Lower your body until you are inches away from the elevated surface. /n 2) Keeping a straight back, push yourself back up until you are in the original starting position, switch sides, repeat.

workout:name: Modified
workout:description: Start: From your knees, place your hands on the ground, under your chest, in an offset position. Move one hand slightly forward, and one hand slightly back. /n 1)  Lower your self to the ground until without turning your body. /n 2) Push yourself back up to the original starting position, switch side, repeat.

workout:name: Staggard
workout:description: Start: Place your hands under your chest in an offset position. Move one hand slightly forward and one hand slightly back. /n 1) Lower yourself to the ground without turning your body. /n 2) Push yourself back up to original starting position, switch sides, repeat.

workout:name: BOSU
workout:description: Start: Place your hands in under your chest, in an offset position on the flat side of the BOSU ball. Move one hand slightly forward and one hand slightly back. /n 1) Lower yourself to the BOSU ball while keeping your body straight. /n 2) Lift yourself back up to the original starting position.

workout:name: Foot Elevation
workout:description: Start: Place your feet on an elevated surface, and hands in a staggard push up position on the flat side of a BOSU ball. /n 1) Lower yourself down to the BOSU ball while keeping your body straight. /n 2) Push your self back up to the original starting position.

workout:name: Modified
workout:description: Start: Place one hand on a medicine ball, and the other on the ground. Both underneath your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders. Have your knees on the ground, and maintain a flat body. /n 1) Keeping a flat body, lower yourself until you are inches away from the ground. /n 2) Push yourself back up to original starting position.

workout:name: Traditional
workout:description: Start: Place one hand on a medicine ball, and the other on the ground. Both underneath your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders. Maintain a flat body with your toes on the ground. /n 1) Lower your body until you are inches away from the ground. /n 2) Push yourself back up to the original starting position.

workout:name: Plyometric with Switch
workout:description: Start: Place one hand on a medicine ball, and the other on the ground. Both underneath your chest, slightly wider than your shoulders. Maintain a flat body with your toes on the ground. /n 1) Lower your body until you are inches away from the ground. /n 2) On the way up, push as hard as you can so that both hands get off of the floor. Simutaneously, switch the medicine ball from one hand to the other. Repeat.

workout:description: Start:

workout:name: Isometric 3 Count
workout:description: Start:

workout:name: On Wall
workout:description: Start: Place on hand on the wall, slightly under your chest. Have your arm extended and your body at an angle. /n 1)  Keeping your body straight, lower yourself until your head is inches away from the wall. /n 2) Push yourself back to the original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Modified Elevated
workout:description: Start: Place one hand on an elevated surface under your chest, and have your knees on the ground. Keep your body as straight as possible. /n 1) Lower your self until your chest is inches away from the elevated surface. /n 2) Push yourself up back to the original starting position.

workout:name: Traditional
workout:description: Start: Place one hand on the ground, with your feet fully extended back like a traditional push up. /n 1) Lower yourself until you chest is inches away from the ground. /n 2) Push yourself back up to the original starting position.

workout:name: Straight Arms
workout:description: Start: Get into a traditional push up position. /n 1) Lower your body by bending your elbows until it is inches away from the ground./n 2) On your way up, push as hard as you can so your hands come off the ground. Keep them straight. Repeat.

workout:name: Claps
workout:description: Start: Get into a traditional push up position. /n 1) Lower your body by bending your elbows until it is inches away from the ground./n 2) On your way up, push as hard as you can so that your hands come off the ground but your toes remain on the ground. /n 3) While in the air, perform a clap with your hands. /n 4) Return to original start position, repeat.

workout:name: Staggard Switch
workout:description: Start: Get into a staggard push up position. /n 1) Lower your body until your chest is inches away from the floor. /n 2) On your way up, push as hard as you can so you hands come off the floor. /n 3) Simultaneously, switch hand positions, and repeat.

workout:name: BOSU
workout:description: Start: Get into a BOSU push up position, with your hands gripping the sides. /n 1) Lower your body until your chest is inches away from the BOSU ball. /n 2) On your way up, push as hard as you can so that you and the BOSU ball get into the air. /n 3) Pull the BOSU ball as close to your chest as possible. /n 4) Return to original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Full Body
workout:description: Start: Get into a traditional push up position. /n 1) Lower your body until your chest is inches away from the floor. /n 2) On your way up, push as hard as you can so that your hands and you feet come off the floor at the same time. /n 3) Return to original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Behind the Back Clap
workout:description: Start: Get into a traditional push up position. /n 1) Lower your body until your chest is inches away from the floor. /n 2) On your way up, push as hard as you can so that your hands go into the air, with your feet staying on the ground. 3) Once you are in the air, clap your hands behind your back! BE CAREFUL!

workout:name: Modified Elevated
workout:description: Start: From your knees, place your hands on an elevated surface, at your sides pointed outwards. /n 1) Lift yourself up until you are in full extension. /n 2) Let yourself back down until your chest is inches away form the ground, repeat.

workout:name: Modified
workout:description: Start: From your knees, place your hands at your sides, facing outwards. /n 1) Keeping a straight body, lift yourself up until you are fully extended. /n 2) Lower yourself back down until you are inches away from the floor, repeat.

workout:name: Traditional
workout:description: Start: Lie face down on the floor. Have your hands at your sides, facing outwards.  /n 1) Keeping a straight back, lift yourself until you are in full extension. /n 2) Lower you self back down, repeat.

workout:name: Elevated
workout:description: Start: Place your feet on an elevated surface, with your arms extended and hands facing outwards at your sides. /n 1) Lower your body until your head is inches away from the floor. /n 2) Push yourself back up you are in the original starting position, repeat.

workout:name: Modified
workout:description: Start: From your knees, lie face down on the floor and extend your arms all the way out to the sides. /n 1) With you palms, lift yourself so you are slightly off the floor, hold for as long as possible, repeat.

workout:name: Regular
workout:description: Start: Lie face down on the floor with your arms extended out to the sides and your feet extended back. /n 1) From your palms, lift your body so you are off the floor, hold for as long as possible, repeat.

workout:name: Jack Knife Push Up
workout:description: Start: Get into jack knife position with your feet on a stability ball. /n 1) Perform a jack knife. /n 2) Continue to do a push up, repeat.
